				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pauli133" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1313727); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1313727&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227564" alt="pauli133" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1313727)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pauli133" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1313727); return false;" >pauli133</a></span> <span class="odate time_1337005487 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 May 2012 14:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1448363">
									

<p>this supports the article pretty well, but some comments:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>R██████: You've come into contact with SCP-1372-1, then?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this reads like a weak literary device. the foundation rep isn't going to refer to the anomaly by number to the local chief.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>(Following this interview, all inhabitants were administered Class A amnesiacs and relocated to an uninhabited atoll in the Marshall Islands.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>i dislike the amnesiac trope to start with, and this is more than a bit beyond belief.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>All remaining documentation regarding the island and SCP-1372 has been destroyed by order of O5 Command, with the exception of Document-1372-1.)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>destroy the documentation? in an organization like this?</p>

							</div>

								
					
