    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-1448369">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-1448369">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1448369)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1448369">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/solan625" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1352778); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1352778&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227564" alt="Solan625" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1352778)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/solan625" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1352778); return false;" >Solan625</a></span> <span class="odate time_1337005948 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 May 2012 14:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1448369">
									

<p>1) Fair enough, I'll switch that to something like &quot;the ships&quot;.</p>
<p>2) These guys have lived all their life 50km from a major cognitohazard with unknown long-term effects. That's the main reason for the amnesiac. In addition, we need to relocate them so we can establish the ACS and so they won't inadvertently tell information to the ACS staff that's above their clearance level - and we don't want them coming back. Relocation and memory restructuring so they think their people have always lived on that atoll is pretty much the only thing I could think of that would effectively accomplish that. I know it's a bit of a trope, but I have a reason for it.</p>
<p>3) That's perhaps a bit poorly worded. What I mean is that anything that the islanders themselves wrote down about SCP-1372 has been destroyed, for reasons related to why this particular interview log is classified. Though maybe I should change that to &quot;archived and classified 4/1372&quot;&#8230; would that be better?</p>

							</div>

								
					
