			<div class="content" id="post-content-1448406">
									

<blockquote>
<p>2) These guys have lived all their life 50km from a major cognitohazard with unknown long-term effects. That's the main reason for the amnesiac. In addition, we need to relocate them so we can establish the ACS and so they won't inadvertently tell information to the ACS staff that's above their clearance level - and we don't want them coming back. Relocation and memory restructuring so they think their people have always lived on that atoll is pretty much the only thing I could think of that would effectively accomplish that. I know it's a bit of a trope, but I have a reason for it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>it's totally understandable - i just find it awkward :p maybe quarantine the island to avoid contact, and put staff on an oil platform? the north sentinel islanders come to mind as well. hell, might make for a more detailed cover story, <em>especially</em> in the context of military exercises.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>3) That's perhaps a bit poorly worded. What I mean is that anything that the islanders themselves wrote down about SCP-1372 has been destroyed, for reasons related to why this particular interview log is classified. Though maybe I should change that to &quot;archived and classified 4/1372&quot;… would that be better?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>i think it would be much better, yes.</p>

